com21HcxStu.name: com21HcxStu
com21HcxStu.contactinfo: Network Management Postal: Paul Gordon Com21, Inc. 750 Tasman Drive Milpitas, California 95035 USA Tel: +1 408 953 9100 Fax: +1 408 953 9299 E-mail: pgordon@com21.com
com21HcxStu.description: This is the Com21 ComPort Control MIB module. All data defined in this MIB is held upon the ComController. COM21 Part# 005-0025-00

hcxStuStatusMacAddr.name: hcxStuStatusMacAddr
hcxStuStatusMacAddr.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device.

hcxStuConfigured.name: hcxStuConfigured
hcxStuConfigured.description: This attribute defines the configured state of the ComPort. This value will be set to true when the NMAPS creates a new entry. If this value is false, the hcxStuAcquired attribute is false and the hcxStuAuthorized flag is set to deauthorized then the entry shall be deleted. Note that this value cannot be set to false if the hcxStuAuthorized flag is set to true.

hcxStuAcquired.name: hcxStuAcquired
hcxStuAcquired.description: This attribute defines the acquired state of the ComPort. Note that is state is set once an ComPort can be managed. We could have a condition were an ComPort is acquired but full service cannot be provided. In that case the hcxStuAcqFailInfo attribute shall indicate a problem. If an unknown ComPort is acquired then an entry is created with this value set to true and both hcxStuAuthorized and hcxStuConfigured set to false.

hcxStuAcqEvent.name: hcxStuAcqEvent
hcxStuAcqEvent.description: This trap is issued only when the acquisition trap is enabled via the hcxStuAcqTrapEnable attribute. Severity WARNING.

hcxStuDeacqEvent.name: hcxStuDeacqEvent
hcxStuDeacqEvent.description: This trap is issued only when the acquisition trap is enabled via the hcxStuAcqTrapEnable attribute. Severity WARNING.

hcxStuAcqFailInfo.name: hcxStuAcqFailInfo
hcxStuAcqFailInfo.description: This attribute provides secondary information related to an ComPort acquisition. If there is a failure in the system that prevents a user from receiving full service, then it will be indicated by this attribute. If an ComPort is unacquired or no problems were encountered then this attribute shall equal noFailure.

hcxStuAuthorized.name: hcxStuAuthorized
hcxStuAuthorized.description: This attribute defines the verified state of the ComPort. This state can only be set by the NMAPS. If this attribute is false, then all cells rates shall be set to 0 on the appropriate Ethernet and RF Receiver cards.

hcxStuLedFlashTest.name: hcxStuLedFlashTest
hcxStuLedFlashTest.description: Used to invoke an ComPort LED test. Setting the the attribute to start will invoke test. Setting to stop will terminate the test. When reading this attribute, nil shall be returned if no test is active and start if the test is in progress.

hcxStuUpstreamTest.name: hcxStuUpstreamTest
hcxStuUpstreamTest.description: Used to invoke an ComPort Upstream RF test. Setting the attribute to start will invoke test. Setting to stop will terminate the test. When reading this attribute, nil shall be returned if no test is active and start if the test is in progress. Note that the hcxStuUpstrmTestFreq shall be validated before initiating the test.

hcxStuVlanId.name: hcxStuVlanId
hcxStuVlanId.description: This attribute defines the virtual LAN id associated with the ComPort. No default, must be set. Note, in the case of an acquired but unconfigured ComPort, a value of 0 will be returned.

hcxStuRxShelfId.name: hcxStuRxShelfId
hcxStuRxShelfId.description: This attribute specifies the shelf id associated with the RX the ComPort is currently assigned to. If ComPort is unacquired then the value shall be 0.

hcxStuRxSlotId.name: hcxStuRxSlotId
hcxStuRxSlotId.description: This attribute specifies the slot id of the RX card to which the ComPort is currently assigned. If ComPort is unacquired then the value shall be 0.

hcxStuRxPortId.name: hcxStuRxPortId
hcxStuRxPortId.description: This attribute specifies the RX port to which the ComPort is assigned. Presently only one port supported. If the ComPort is unacquired then the attribute shall be set to 0.

hcxStuServiceType.name: hcxStuServiceType
hcxStuServiceType.description: This attribute defines the Service Type associated with the ComPort. This equals the associated hcxServiceTypeId attribute. The default shall be 0, indicating no assigned service type.

hcxStuConfSwImage.name: hcxStuConfSwImage
hcxStuConfSwImage.description: Contains the configured software image to be downloaded to the ComPort. The Common Controller download process shall check this value when a download is requested. If this image does not support the hardware specified by the ComPort then an incompatible software version trap shall be generated. It is then up to the user to correct this field. When this field is set, the agent shall check if there is an image of the specified type loaded. If this is not the case then a unavailable software version trap shall be generated. Again, it is the responsibility of the user to ensure that the required image is downloaded. The image identifier shall be represented by 4 numbers deliminated by periods. i.e. a.b.c.d. Each number shall have a value between 0 and 255. This allows storage within a single (four byte) word.

hcxIncompSwVersion.name: hcxIncompSwVersion
hcxIncompSwVersion.description: This trap is issued if the configured sw version (in hcxStuConfSwImage) is not applicable to the hw version/hw options reported by the ComPort. This an event with no clear condition. Only severity is WARNING.

hcxUnavailSwVersion.name: hcxUnavailSwVersion
hcxUnavailSwVersion.description: This trap is issued if the configured image cannot be located on the ComController. This an event with no clear condition. Only severity is WARNING.

hcxStuPingTestAction.name: hcxStuPingTestAction
hcxStuPingTestAction.description: Used to invoke a ping of the ComPort. Sends an OAM Ping message. When the user reads this attribute a nil response shall be given if no test is active and execute shall be return if a test is active.

hcxStuPingTestComplete.name: hcxStuPingTestComplete
hcxStuPingTestComplete.description: This trap is issued when the ping test is completed. This an event with no clear condition. Only severity is WARNING.

hcxStuPingTestResult.name: hcxStuPingTestResult
hcxStuPingTestResult.description: contains result of last ping test. invalid is returned if ping test cannot be run. Examples being an unacquired ComPort or a ComPort.

hcxStuEthTestAction.name: hcxStuEthTestAction
hcxStuEthTestAction.description: This attribute is used to invoke the ComPort Ethernet test. If lpBkTest is selected, the ComController will place the ComPort in the loopback state, transmit a number of ethernet packets and validate the returned packets. hcxStuEthLpbkTestUpRate and hcxStuEthLpbkTestLatency attributes contain the Rate and Latency for the upstream path If dnStrmTest is selected, the ComController will transmit a number of ethernet packets and calculate the downstream rate. hcxStuEthTestDnRate attribute will contain the rate for the downstream path.

hcxStuEthTestComplete.name: hcxStuEthTestComplete
hcxStuEthTestComplete.description: This notification is generated whenever the ComPort loopback test is completed. This shall either be completed after reception of looped back packet(s) or after a timeout. This an event with no clear condition. Only severity is WARNING.

hcxStuEthTestResult.name: hcxStuEthTestResult
hcxStuEthTestResult.description: This attribute contains the result of the last ComPort test.

hcxStuRetPathSelect.name: hcxStuRetPathSelect
hcxStuRetPathSelect.description: This attribute specifies the return path mode of the ComPort. Default is two way cable.

hcxStuAcqRangeFail.name: hcxStuAcqRangeFail
hcxStuAcqRangeFail.description: This trap is issued if an RX card reports a failure to range a previously acquired ComPort. Note that the ComPort states are defined in the proxy ComPort MIB. This an event with no clear condition. Only severity is WARNING.

hcxStuAcqOnlineFail.name: hcxStuAcqOnlineFail
hcxStuAcqOnlineFail.description: This trap is issued if an RX card successfully acquires an ComPort, but the ComPort cannot be placed online due to a ComController or ComPort failure. Only severity is WARNING.

hcxStuEth8022Filter.name: hcxStuEth8022Filter
hcxStuEth8022Filter.description: This attribute is used to control the filtering of 802.2 Ethernet packets for a specific ComPORT. When this is enabled (true), all Ethernet packets of this type shall be dropped. Default is true.

hcxStuDnstrmFwdCntrl.name: hcxStuDnstrmFwdCntrl
hcxStuDnstrmFwdCntrl.description: This attribute is used to control the forwarding of packets downstream which where received in the upstream from a specific ComPORT. If set to true, then the data will NOT be forwarded downstream but out the WAN interface only. Default is true. Not that the logic here is reversed when compared to the hcxVlanPeerToPeerFlag attribute in the VLAN group.

hcxStuStatsCollect.name: hcxStuStatsCollect
hcxStuStatsCollect.description: This attribute is used to control whether statistics are collected periodically from the ComPort. Default is enable for two-way ComPorts and disable for ComPorts configured for telephone return operation.

hcxStuPowerRangeState.name: hcxStuPowerRangeState
hcxStuPowerRangeState.description: This attribute describes the power ranging state of the ComPort. An unacquired ComPort or one operating within the power specifications shall have a state of noProblem.

hcxStuRangFailPowerLow.name: hcxStuRangFailPowerLow
hcxStuRangFailPowerLow.description: This trap is generated when the RX card cannot set a ComPort's power level correctly - the ComPort has too low a power level. This alarm is generated once and cleared only when the condition is corrected or the ComPort is deacquired. Default severity is MINOR.

hcxStuRangFailLowClear.name: hcxStuRangFailLowClear
hcxStuRangFailLowClear.description: This trap is generated when the RX card successful ranges a ComPort that was previously reported as in the low power state or when a ComPort in that state is deacquired. Severity is CLEARED.

hcxStuRangFailPowerHigh.name: hcxStuRangFailPowerHigh
hcxStuRangFailPowerHigh.description: This trap is generated when the RX card cannot set a ComPort's power level correctly - the ComPort has too high a power level. This alarm is generated once and cleared only when the condition is corrected or the ComPort is deacquired. Default severity is MINOR.

hcxStuRangFailHighClear.name: hcxStuRangFailHighClear
hcxStuRangFailHighClear.description: This trap is generated when the RX card successful ranges a ComPort that was previously reported as in the high power state or when a ComPort in that state is deacquired. Severity is CLEARED.

hcxStuRpmIPortId.name: hcxStuRpmIPortId
hcxStuRpmIPortId.description: This attribute specifies the RPM I-Port to which the ComPort is associated. 0 will be reported if the ComPort has never been acquired or is not connected via an RPM. The last known I-Port will be reported if the ComPort is unacquired but have been acquired previously.

hcxStuEthLpbkTestUpRate.name: hcxStuEthLpbkTestUpRate
hcxStuEthLpbkTestUpRate.description: This attribute contains the rate recorded for the last loopback test. Will be 0 if test failed.

hcxStuEthLpbkTestLatency.name: hcxStuEthLpbkTestLatency
hcxStuEthLpbkTestLatency.description: This attribute contains the round trip packet latency recorded by the last loopback test. Again 0 if test failed.

hcxStuModelName.name: hcxStuModelName
hcxStuModelName.description: This attribute defines the ComPort Model Type read from the ComPort. Prior to the acquisition of the ComPort for the first time, this attribute will be uninitialized. Invalid will be set if the model number is not recongnized.

hcxStuEthTestDnRate.name: hcxStuEthTestDnRate
hcxStuEthTestDnRate.description: This attribute contains the downstream rate (in bps) recorded by the last hcxStuEthTestAction test. 0 if test failed.

hcxStuEthLpbkTestDuration.name: hcxStuEthLpbkTestDuration
hcxStuEthLpbkTestDuration.description: This attribute specifies the duration of the loopback test in seconds. Default is 5 seconds.

com21HcxStuSrcIpAddrEntry.name: com21HcxStuSrcIpAddrEntry
com21HcxStuSrcIpAddrEntry.description: Holds the IP addresses and associated masks for ARP filtering. There are 8 addresses per ComPort.

hcxStuSrcIpAddrMacAddr.name: hcxStuSrcIpAddrMacAddr
hcxStuSrcIpAddrMacAddr.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device.

hcxStuSrcIpAddrIPAddr.name: hcxStuSrcIpAddrIPAddr
hcxStuSrcIpAddrIPAddr.description: allowable IP Address for ComPort. Default 0.0.0.0.

hcxStuSrcIpAddrIPMask.name: hcxStuSrcIpAddrIPMask
hcxStuSrcIpAddrIPMask.description: IP mask for ComPort. Default is ff.ff.ff.ff.

hcxStuSrcIpAddrUserMacAddr.name: hcxStuSrcIpAddrUserMacAddr
hcxStuSrcIpAddrUserMacAddr.description: allowable MAC Address for ComPort. Default is 0:0:0:0:0:0

hcxStuSrcIpAddrIPStatus.name: hcxStuSrcIpAddrIPStatus
hcxStuSrcIpAddrIPStatus.description: Used to delete or create an entry.

hcxStuSrcIpAddrEtherIPAddr.name: hcxStuSrcIpAddrEtherIPAddr
hcxStuSrcIpAddrEtherIPAddr.description: IP address of Ethernet Interface on users PC. Applicable only to telephone return.

hcxStuSrcIpAddrType.name: hcxStuSrcIpAddrType
hcxStuSrcIpAddrType.description: This attribute indicates if the specified IP address/mask combination is Statically configured by NMAPS or dynamically learnt via DHCP

hcxStuSrcIpAddrLeaseTimer.name: hcxStuSrcIpAddrLeaseTimer
hcxStuSrcIpAddrLeaseTimer.description: This attribute indicates the lease timer value associated with a dynamically learnt IP address

com21HcxStuDstIpAddrEntry.name: com21HcxStuDstIpAddrEntry
com21HcxStuDstIpAddrEntry.description: Holds the IP addresses and associated masks for ARP filtering. There are 8 addresses per ComPort.

hcxStuDstIpAddrMacAddr.name: hcxStuDstIpAddrMacAddr
hcxStuDstIpAddrMacAddr.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device.

hcxStuDstIpAddrIPAddr.name: hcxStuDstIpAddrIPAddr
hcxStuDstIpAddrIPAddr.description: allowable IP Address for ComPort. Default 0.0.0.0.

hcxStuDstIpAddrIPMask.name: hcxStuDstIpAddrIPMask
hcxStuDstIpAddrIPMask.description: IP mask for ComPort. Default is ff.ff.ff.ff.

hcxStuDstIpAddrIPStatus.name: hcxStuDstIpAddrIPStatus
hcxStuDstIpAddrIPStatus.description: Used to delete or create an entry.

hcxStuIpFiltMacAddr.name: hcxStuIpFiltMacAddr
hcxStuIpFiltMacAddr.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device.

hcxStuIpArpFiltEnable.name: hcxStuIpArpFiltEnable
hcxStuIpArpFiltEnable.description: Specifies whether ARP authentication filtering should be enabled for this ComPort. This filter is applicable to 10BT, 100BT, and OC3 cards. It filters traffic in the upstream direction. Default is false. This filter can also be enabled for an entire VLAN via the MIB attribute hcxVlanIpArpFiltEnbl.

hcxStuIpArpFiltInvalidAddr.name: hcxStuIpArpFiltInvalidAddr
hcxStuIpArpFiltInvalidAddr.description: Contains the last invalid IP Address used by the ComPort. This value is cleared on the quarter hour.

hcxStuArpInvalidAddr.name: hcxStuArpInvalidAddr
hcxStuArpInvalidAddr.description: this trap is generated whenever an invalid ARP IP source address is detected. Severity is WARNING.

hcxStuIpArpFiltBadServAddr.name: hcxStuIpArpFiltBadServAddr
hcxStuIpArpFiltBadServAddr.description: Contains the last ComController Server IP Address used by the ComPort. This value is cleared on the quarter hour.

hcxStuArpBadServerAddr.name: hcxStuArpBadServerAddr
hcxStuArpBadServerAddr.description: this trap is generated whenever the ComPort is detected as utilizing a reserved server address as its source IP address. Severity is WARNING.

hcxStuIpSrcFiltEnable.name: hcxStuIpSrcFiltEnable
hcxStuIpSrcFiltEnable.description: Specifies whether IP source address filtering should be enabled for this ComPort. This filter is applicable to 100BT, and OC3 cards. It is not applicable to 10BT card. It filters traffic in the upstream direction. Default is false. This filter can also be enabled for an entire VLAN via the MIB attribute hcxVlanIpSrcFiltEnbl.

hcxStuIpDstFiltEnable.name: hcxStuIpDstFiltEnable
hcxStuIpDstFiltEnable.description: Specifies whether IP destination address filtering should be enabled for this ComPort. This filter is applicable to 100BT, and OC3 cards. It is not applicable to to 10BT card. It filters traffic in the upstream direction. Default is false. This filter can also be enabled for an entire VLAN via the MIB attribute hcxVlanIpDstFiltEnbl.

hcxStuIpBootpReqFiltEnbl.name: hcxStuIpBootpReqFiltEnbl
hcxStuIpBootpReqFiltEnbl.description: Allows enabling or disabling BOOTP Request Filter for this STU. Default: FALSE

hcxStuIpBootpReplyFiltEnbl.name: hcxStuIpBootpReplyFiltEnbl
hcxStuIpBootpReplyFiltEnbl.description: Specifies whether BOOTP replies, or DHCPOFFER, or DHCPACK packets should be filtered for this ComPort. This filter is applicable to 100BT, and OC3 cards. It it not applicable to 10BT card. It filters traffic in the upstream direction. Default is false. This filter can also be enabled for an entire VLAN via the MIB attribute hcxVlanIpBootpReplyFiltEnbl.

hcxStuIpDhcpSnoopFiltEnbl.name: hcxStuIpDhcpSnoopFiltEnbl
hcxStuIpDhcpSnoopFiltEnbl.description: Specifies whether DHCP snooping should be enabled for this ComPort. This filter is applicable to 100BT, and OC3 cards. It is not applicable to 10BT card. It snoops traffic in the downstream direction for DHCPACK packets, and in the upstream direction for DHCPDECLINE or DHCPRELEASE packets. Dynamic IP address assigments thus learned are stored in the valid source IP address table (com21HcxStuSrcIpAddrGroup.) Default is false. This filter can also be enabled for an entire VLAN via the MIB attribute hcxVlanIpDhcpSnoopFiltEnbl.

hcxStuL2SnapFiltEnbl.name: hcxStuL2SnapFiltEnbl
hcxStuL2SnapFiltEnbl.description: Specifies whether SNAP-encoded IEEE 802.3 packets should be filtered for this ComPort. This filter is applicable to 100BT, and OC3 cards. It is not applicable to 10BT card. It filters traffic in both upstream and downstream directions. Default is false. This filter can also be enabled for an entire VLAN via the MIB attribute hcxVlanL2SnapFiltEnbl.

hcxStuL2NonSnapFiltEnbl.name: hcxStuL2NonSnapFiltEnbl
hcxStuL2NonSnapFiltEnbl.description: Specifies whether non-SNAP-encoded IEEE 802.3 packets should be filtered for this ComPort. This filter is applicable to 10BT, 100BT, and OC3 cards. It filters traffic in both upstream and downstream directions. Default is false. This filter can also be enabled for an entire VLAN via the MIB attribute hcxVlanL2NonSnapFiltEnbl.

hcxStuL2EnetFiltEnbl.name: hcxStuL2EnetFiltEnbl
hcxStuL2EnetFiltEnbl.description: Specifies whether Ethernet packets should be filtered for this ComPort. This filter is applicable to 100BT and OC3 cards. It is not applicable to 10BT card. It filters traffic in both upstream and downstream directions. Default is false. This filter can also be enabled for an entire VLAN via the MIB attribute hcxVlanL2EnetFiltEnbl.

hcxStuL2ArpIpv4FiltEnbl.name: hcxStuL2ArpIpv4FiltEnbl
hcxStuL2ArpIpv4FiltEnbl.description: Specifies whether ARP packets should be filtered for this ComPort. This filter is applicable to 100BT and OC3 cards. It is not applicable to 10BT card. It filters traffic in both upstream and downstream directions. Default is false. This filter can also be enabled for an entire VLAN via the MIB attribute hcxVlanL2ArpIpv4FiltEnbl.

hcxStuL2Ipv4FiltEnbl.name: hcxStuL2Ipv4FiltEnbl
hcxStuL2Ipv4FiltEnbl.description: Specifies whether IPv4 packets should be filtered for this ComPort. This filter is applicable to 100BT and OC3 cards. It is not applicable to 10BT card. It filters traffic in both upstream and downstream directions. Default is false. This filter can also be enabled for an entire VLAN via the MIB attribute hcxVlanL2Ipv4FiltEnbl.

hcxStuL2Ipv6FiltEnbl.name: hcxStuL2Ipv6FiltEnbl
hcxStuL2Ipv6FiltEnbl.description: Specifies whether IPv6 packets should be filtered for this ComPort. This filter is applicable to 100BT and OC3 cards. It is not applicable to 10BT card. It filters traffic in both upstream and downstream directions. Default is false. This filter can also be enabled for an entire VLAN via the MIB attribute hcxVlanL2Ipv6FiltEnbl.

hcxStuL2IpxFiltEnbl.name: hcxStuL2IpxFiltEnbl
hcxStuL2IpxFiltEnbl.description: Specifies whether IPX packets should be filtered for this ComPort. This filter is applicable to 100BT and OC3 cards. It is not applicable to 10BT card. It filters traffic in both upstream and downstream directions. Default is false. This filter can also be enabled for an entire VLAN via the MIB attribute hcxVlanL2IpxFiltEnbl.

hcxStuL2AppletalkFiltEnbl.name: hcxStuL2AppletalkFiltEnbl
hcxStuL2AppletalkFiltEnbl.description: Specifies whether AppleTalk packets should be filtered for this ComPort. This filter is applicable to 100BT and OC3 cards. It is not applicable to 10BT card. It filters traffic in both upstream and downstream directions. Default is false. This filter can also be enabled for an entire VLAN via the MIB attribute hcxVlanL2AppleTalkFiltEnbl.

hcxStuL2OthersFiltEnbl.name: hcxStuL2OthersFiltEnbl
hcxStuL2OthersFiltEnbl.description: Specifies whether all layer 2 packets that are none of the above (ARP, IPv4, IPv6, IPX, AppleTalk) should be filtered for this ComPort. This filter is applicable to 100BT and OC3 cards. It is not applicable to 10BT card. This filter filters traffic in both directions. This filter can also be enabled for an entire VLAN via the MIB attribute hcxVlanL2OthersFiltEnbl. Default is false.

hcxStuIpNetbiosFiltEnbl.name: hcxStuIpNetbiosFiltEnbl
hcxStuIpNetbiosFiltEnbl.description: Specifies whether NetBIOS-over-IP packets should be filtered for this ComPort. This filter is applicable to 100BT and OC3 cards. It is not applicable to 10BT card. This filter filters traffic in the upstream direction. Default is false. This filter can also be enabled for an entire VLAN via the MIB attribute hcxVlanIpNetbiosFiltEnbl.

hcxStuIpFiltStatsMacAddr.name: hcxStuIpFiltStatsMacAddr
hcxStuIpFiltStatsMacAddr.description: Contains IEEE 802 medium access control address of the ComPort device.

hcxStuIpCurrArpFiltStat.name: hcxStuIpCurrArpFiltStat
hcxStuIpCurrArpFiltStat.description: Contains the number of ARP packets from this ComPort dropped due to authentication filtering in the current 15 minute collection period.

hcxStuIpCurrSrcFiltStat.name: hcxStuIpCurrSrcFiltStat
hcxStuIpCurrSrcFiltStat.description: Contains the number of IP packets from this ComPort dropped due to source address filtering in the current 15 minute collection period.

hcxStuIpCurrDstFiltStat.name: hcxStuIpCurrDstFiltStat
hcxStuIpCurrDstFiltStat.description: Contains the number of IP packets from this ComPort dropped due to destination address filtering in the current 15 minute collection period.

hcxStuIpCurrBootpReqFiltStat.name: hcxStuIpCurrBootpReqFiltStat
hcxStuIpCurrBootpReqFiltStat.description: Contains the number of bootp Req packets from this ComPort dropped due to filtering in the current 15 minute collection period.

hcxStuIpCurrBootpReplyFiltStat.name: hcxStuIpCurrBootpReplyFiltStat
hcxStuIpCurrBootpReplyFiltStat.description: Contains the number of bootp Reply packets from this ComPort dropped due to filtering in the current 15 minute collection period.

hcxStuIpCurrDhcpSnoopFiltStat.name: hcxStuIpCurrDhcpSnoopFiltStat
hcxStuIpCurrDhcpSnoopFiltStat.description: Contains the number of DHCP Ack packets from this ComPort snooped due to filtering in the current 15 minute collection period.

hcxStuIpPrevArpFiltStat.name: hcxStuIpPrevArpFiltStat
hcxStuIpPrevArpFiltStat.description: Contains the number of ARP packets from this ComPort dropped due to authentication filtering in the previous 15 minute collection period.

hcxStuIpPrevSrcFiltStat.name: hcxStuIpPrevSrcFiltStat
hcxStuIpPrevSrcFiltStat.description: Contains the number of IP packets from this ComPort dropped due to source address filtering in the previous 15 minute collection period.

hcxStuIpPrevDstFiltStat.name: hcxStuIpPrevDstFiltStat
hcxStuIpPrevDstFiltStat.description: Contains the number of IP packets from this ComPort dropped due to destination address filtering in the previous 15 minute collection period.

hcxStuIpPrevBootpReqFiltStat.name: hcxStuIpPrevBootpReqFiltStat
hcxStuIpPrevBootpReqFiltStat.description: Contains the number of bootp Req packets from this ComPort dropped due to filtering in the previous 15 minute collection period.

hcxStuIpPrevBootpReplyFiltStat.name: hcxStuIpPrevBootpReplyFiltStat
hcxStuIpPrevBootpReplyFiltStat.description: Contains the number of bootp Reply packets from this ComPort dropped due to filtering in the previous 15 minute collection period.

hcxStuIpPrevDhcpSnoopFiltStat.name: hcxStuIpPrevDhcpSnoopFiltStat
hcxStuIpPrevDhcpSnoopFiltStat.description: Contains the number of DHCP Ack packets from this ComPort snooped due to filtering in the previous 15 minute collection period.

hcxStuIpClearStats.name: hcxStuIpClearStats
hcxStuIpClearStats.description: This attribute is used to clear all IP Filter statistics counters in this group. This operation is only possible if the hcxStatsControl attribute is set to wrapCurr.

hcxStuL2CurrSnapFiltStat.name: hcxStuL2CurrSnapFiltStat
hcxStuL2CurrSnapFiltStat.description: Contains the number of SNAP-encoded IEEE 802.3 packets filtered in the current 15 min collection period.

hcxStuL2CurrNonSnapFiltStat.name: hcxStuL2CurrNonSnapFiltStat
hcxStuL2CurrNonSnapFiltStat.description: Contains the number of non-SNAP-encoded IEEE 802.3 packets filtered in the current 15 min collection period.

hcxStuL2CurrEnetFiltStat.name: hcxStuL2CurrEnetFiltStat
hcxStuL2CurrEnetFiltStat.description: Contains the number of Ethernet packets filtered in the current 15 min collection period.

hcxStuL2CurrArpIpv4FiltStat.name: hcxStuL2CurrArpIpv4FiltStat
hcxStuL2CurrArpIpv4FiltStat.description: Contains the number of ARP for IPv4 packets filtered in the current 15 min collection period.

hcxStuL2CurrIpv4FiltStat.name: hcxStuL2CurrIpv4FiltStat
hcxStuL2CurrIpv4FiltStat.description: Contains the number of IPv4 packets filtered in the current 15 min collection period.

hcxStuL2CurrIpv6FiltStat.name: hcxStuL2CurrIpv6FiltStat
hcxStuL2CurrIpv6FiltStat.description: Contains the number of IPv6 packets filtered in the current 15 min collection period.

hcxStuL2CurrIpxFiltStat.name: hcxStuL2CurrIpxFiltStat
hcxStuL2CurrIpxFiltStat.description: Contains the number of IPX packets filtered in the current 15 min collection period.

hcxStuL2CurrAppletalkFiltStat.name: hcxStuL2CurrAppletalkFiltStat
hcxStuL2CurrAppletalkFiltStat.description: Contains the number of Appletalk packets filtered in the current 15 min collection period.

hcxStuL2CurrOthersFiltStat.name: hcxStuL2CurrOthersFiltStat
